character-confusion 08-Jun-20 11:27 PM
@SetToBlow these are the full rules Also, everyone can make a proposal for a bill if they get 10 people to endorse the bill (including themself). When they have gathered the required 10 supporters, they dm a mod detailing the plan of the bill. A google doc will be put up accompanied by a voting system based on emojis as usual. The person who proposed the bill may ask for a senate meeting. This meeting is not required and just if they want to give some extra explanation to the senate. Other senators can dm a mod if they wish to debate against said bill if they don't agree with it. The senate meeting may be held at minimum 8 hours after the proposal for the bill to make sure people can tune in if they want. The voting will be up for 24 hours. In order to pass, it needs 50% of the votes+1 vote
